SimPill

SimPill is an iOS application developed using Swift 5 and Xcode. It features a calendar user interface that helps elderly users keep track of their medication schedules and supplies. The app also allows users to share their progress with others and includes a tutorial to help users get familiarized with its interface.

Getting Started

SimPill can be downloaded from the App Store or can be built from the source code available on GitHub. To build the app, clone the repository and open the project file in Xcode.

Prerequisites
Xcode 12 or higher
iOS 14 or higher
Installing
SimPill can be downloaded for free from the App Store. To build the app from source, clone the repository and open the project file in Xcode. Then, build and run the app on a simulator or a connected iOS device.

Features

Medication schedule tracking
Medication supply tracking
Progress sharing with others
Tutorial for first-time users
License

SimPill is not currently licensed and is available on the App Store for free download.

Acknowledgments

This app was developed as a personal project to help elderly users keep track of their medication schedules and supplies.